### Form

Easily create nicely looking forms with different styles and layouts. Forms are built with a combination of standard form elements, 
as well as the Grid .col-* system.

> To apply form component, use .form class on a <form> or any other parent element that contains form elements.

You can style your form elements individually or you can style those using a parent-child classes. 
Parent - child classes are added to the main .form element. You can use any of the color.css modifier 
classes on your .form element to style all of the containing child elements. 
There are also two custom parent-child form modifiers: .wire for creating wire forms (line based form elements) 
and .border for creating bordered forms as shown in example below.

> When creating bordered forms, you can change border width of your form elements by adding one of the border 
> width modifier classes to your form element .border-*width. *width can be from 2 up to 4.

