### Add-on

You can add addons to your input elements by wrapping those inside a .addon-prepend for inserting addons 
before an input and .addon-append for inserting addons after an input. We've chosen this approach so that 
we can have more control over addon wrapped elements, for example when adding styles or thicker border or 
applying different sizes to our input elements.

An addon inside a addon-wrapper is a separate element which can have a .prepend or .append class. 
.addon-prepend wrapper is to include a .prepend addon element and .addon-append wrapper is to include a 
.append addon element. You can also include both addons at the same time by adding .addon-prepend .addon-append 
class to your wrapper which will is to include both .prepend and .append addons. 
See example below.

##### Addon Prepend

##### html
----------

```
<form class="form green">
  <label>Addon Prepend <span class="require">*</span></label>
  <div class="addon-prepend">
    <span class="prepend btn"><i class="fa fa-user"></i></span>
    <input type="text" placeholder="addon prepend">
  </div>
</form>
```

##### Addon Append

##### html
----------

```
<form class="form green">
  <label>Addon Append <span class="require">*</span></label>
  <div class="addon-append">
    <input type="text" placeholder="addon append">
    <span class="append btn"><i class="fa fa-user"></i></span>
  </div>
</form>
```

##### Addon Prepend + Addon Append

##### html
----------

```
<form class="form green">
  <label>Addon Prepend + Addon Append <span class="require">*</span></label>
  <div class="addon-prepend addon-append">
    <span class="prepend btn"><i class="fa fa-user"></i></span>
    <input type="text" placeholder="addon prepend * append">
    <span class="append btn"><i class="fa fa-cloud"></i></span>
